list.text:
Discord Emojis Complete List

Original graphics by Twemoji - https://twemoji.twitter.com/

Exported to Desmos by harry7557558 - https://github.com/harry7557558/miscellaneous/tree/master/twemoji-to-desmos

A summary of the steps to produce this graph:

- Scrap emojis from Discord, arrange them on a generalized Hilbert curve
- Read Bézier splines from the SVG file, apply arc-length parameterization and approximate them using a list of points
- Apply Fast Fourier Transform to the points list, normalize, scale by a factor, and round amplitudes to the nearest integer; this allows less significant waves to be discarded
- Merge shapes with the same color into one expression to save bytes; this requires resolving layering relationships, which can be done using a greedy algorithm
- Pull out repeated expressions and store them in definitions
- Generate a JSON file containing the expressions that can be exported to Desmos

Further improvements may be made to reduce graph size:

- Use a better greedy algorithm to merge shapes
- Merge shapes into lists of equations and lists of colors; It is estimated that this can save 20%-40% of the graph size
- Detect shapes that are mirror images when pulling out repeated expressions
